            "category": "crypto",
            "date": "2025-02-19",
            "headline": "Cryptocurrencies Bitcoin, Ethereum, Dogecoin dropped amidst stock market surge; Bitcoin at $95,525.86, Ethereum at $2,674.93. Liquidations hit $345M, fear index rises, $800M in short positions at risk if BTC reclaims $100K.",
            "id": "a1658393-5032-4563-af7c-4d60858e3183",
            "is_major": false,
            "source": "Benzinga",
            "source_type": "news",
            "summary": "Leading cryptocurrencies experienced a dip on Tuesday despite record highs in the stock market. Bitcoin saw a decrease of 0.14% down to $95,525.86, while Ethereum dropped by 1.96% to $2,674.93, and Dogecoin fell by 2.19% to $0.2515 at 7:45 p.m. ET. Bitcoin hit a two-week low of $93,388.83, breaking its rangebound pattern. Ethereum also plummeted before recovering slightly. Bitcoin's dominance in the market rose above 60%, with Ethereum holding a 10.3% share. Cryptocurrency liquidations surged to $344.95 million in 24 hours, erasing over $278 million in bets. Bitcoin's Open Interest rose by 1.12%, signifying new short positions. Market sentiment shifted to \"Fear\" on the Crypto Fear & Greed Index, possibly leading to increased short positions. If Bitcoin reaches $100,000, over $800 million in short positions could be liquidated.",
