            "id": "056f59e4-c2e8-4a9d-9614-9bd787efb783",
            "is_major": false,
            "source": "GlobeNewswire",
            "source_type": "news",
            "summary": "In the quarter ending on December 31, 2024, the Daily Journal Corporation (NASDAQ: DJCO) reported consolidated revenues of $17,704,000, marking a significant increase from $15,993,000 in the same period the previous year. This rise of $1,711,000 was primarily driven by boosts in Journal Technologies\u2019 license and maintenance fees amounting to $968,000, and other public service fees increasing by $1,242,000. However, there was a decrease in consulting fees of $703,000 which partially offset the overall revenue growth. Additionally, the Traditional Business sector saw a rise in advertising revenues by $192,000 and advertising service fees and other revenues by $27,000 during this period.",
